description:
Nvidia’s RTX 5060 Ti is here... and yes there is still an 8GB version in 2025. We're focusing on the 16GB model though, and in this review we break down performance, ray tracing, DLSS 4, and where this GPU actually makes sense in today’s market. Read the full written review here: https://www.kitguru.net/components/graphic-cards/dominic-moass/nvidia-rtx-5060-ti-16gb-review-ft-gigabyte-palit/

TEST SYSTEM POWERED BY MSI. Watch the full video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pAD8k9MqJa0&ab_channel=KitGuruTech  Shop here: https://msi.gm/S5DEB4CD

CPU: AMD Ryzen 7 9800X3D
Motherboard: MSI MPG X870E Carbon WiFi
Memory: 64GB (2x32GB) Kingston Fury Beast DDR5 6000MHz CL30
SSD: 4TB Kingston NV3 Gen 4 PCIe NVMe
Chassis: MSI MPG Gungnir 300R Airflow
CPU Cooler: MSI MAG CoreLiquid i360
Power Supply: MSI MEG Ai1300P
Operating System: Windows 11 23H2
Monitor: MSI MPG 321URX QD-OLED
Resizable BAR: Enabled for all supported GPUs

We never offer affiliate links or take percentages of product sales in any review we create. If we say the product is good or bad we mean it. Our Editor in chief wrote about why you should value this and how the industry is rife with fake reviews from 'influencers' - read here https://bit.ly/3pXzaw4
